@startuml uc6_export_part_2
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title UC-06 Part 2: Report Generation Pipeline

participant "RabbitMQ\n(export.jobs)" as MQ
participant "Export Worker\n(Python)" as Worker
database "PostgreSQL\n(analytics data)" as DB
participant "MinIO\n(Object Storage)" as MinIO
database "PostgreSQL\n(export_requests)" as ExportDB
participant "RabbitMQ\n(notifications)" as NotifyMQ

== Consume Export Request ==

MQ -> Worker: CONSUME export.requested event\n{\n  "export_request_id": "uuid",\n  "project_id": "uuid",\n  "format": "pdf",\n  "config": {...}\n}
activate Worker

Worker -> Worker: Parse event payload\nExtract: export_request_id,\n  project_id, format, config

== Query Analytics Data ==

Worker -> DB: SELECT * FROM posts\nWHERE project_id = :project_id\n  AND created_at BETWEEN :start AND :end
activate DB

DB --> Worker: Return analytics data:\n- Posts with sentiment\n- Aspect analysis\n- Competitor comparison\n- Crisis posts\n- Aggregated metrics
deactivate DB

Worker -> Worker: Transform data for report:\n- Group by sentiment\n- Calculate statistics\n- Prepare charts data

== Generate Report File ==

alt Format = PDF

    Worker -> Worker: Use WeasyPrint library:\n1. Render HTML template\n2. Embed charts (matplotlib)\n3. Format tables\n4. Generate PDF binary

else Format = Excel

    Worker -> Worker: Use openpyxl library:\n1. Create workbook\n2. Add sheets: Overview,\n   Sentiment, Competitor, Crisis\n3. Insert data và charts\n4. Generate .xlsx binary

else Format = CSV

    Worker -> Worker: Use csv library:\n1. Flatten data structure\n2. Write comma-separated rows\n3. Generate .csv text file

end

Worker -> Worker: File generated:\nSize: 2.5 MB\nFilename: {project_name}_report_{date}.{format}

== Upload to MinIO ==

Worker -> MinIO: PUT object\nBucket: reports\nKey: projects/{project_id}/exports/{export_request_id}.{format}\nContent-Type: application/{format}
activate MinIO

MinIO --> Worker: 200 OK\nObject uploaded successfully
deactivate MinIO

Worker -> MinIO: Generate pre-signed URL\nExpiry: 7 days (604800 seconds)
activate MinIO

MinIO --> Worker: Pre-signed download URL:\nhttps://minio.smap.local/reports/...\n?X-Amz-Expires=604800&...
deactivate MinIO

== Update Export Request Status ==

Worker -> ExportDB: UPDATE export_requests\nSET status = 'completed',\n    download_url = :url,\n    file_size = :size,\n    completed_at = NOW()\nWHERE id = :export_request_id
activate ExportDB

ExportDB --> Worker: 1 row updated
deactivate ExportDB

== Publish Completion Event ==

Worker -> NotifyMQ: PUBLISH to exchange: smap.events\nRouting key: export.completed\nPayload:\n{\n  "event_type": "export.completed",\n  "payload": {\n    "export_request_id": "uuid",\n    "project_id": "uuid",\n    "user_id": "uuid",\n    "download_url": "...",\n    "file_size": 2621440,\n    "format": "pdf"\n  }\n}
activate NotifyMQ

NotifyMQ --> Worker: ACK (published)
deactivate NotifyMQ

Worker -> MQ: ACK original message\n(export.requested consumed)
deactivate Worker

note over Worker, NotifyMQ
  Export job completed successfully.
  Notification sent to WebSocket service
  for real-time user notification.
end note

== Exception Handling ==

note over Worker, ExportDB
  If export fails (timeout > 10 min, DB error, OOM):
  1. Update status = 'failed', reason = error_message
  2. Publish export.failed event
  3. NACK message (retry or DLQ)
end note

@enduml
